Author:
Vol / Page:  19
Edition:
Quote:   The timber on the western side consists of red- and white-pine, matai (or black-pine), totara, kawhaka (or cedar), rata, and occasional silver-pine, besides black- and red-birch (<i>Fagus fusca</i>). <i>Ibid.</i> 30 The timbers of commercial value are totara, rimu, miro, matai, rata, and kamahi, in mixed bushes; but <i>Fagus fusca</i> and other beeches predominate on the high lands between the lakes and the fiords on the west coast.
